    .question Q. How do I convert a video?
    p Converting videos is easy. Contact FOREVER media services by calling 1-888-FOREVER to receive your custom quote.

    .question Q. What photo and media file formats does FOREVER accept?
    p FOREVER will convert any legacy media and files to high quality digital formats best suited for long term preservation.This includes video tapes (VHS, beta NTSC, VHS-C, Hi-8, MiniDV), film reels (8mm, Super-8, 16mm), slides (plastic or cardboard frames), physical photos, CD and DVD, memory cards, memory sticks, hard drives, compact flash cards (SD, SM, MMC, MS, CF, xD-Picture Cards, USB drives), and physical documents. Existing digital files may be uploaded in Microsoft Word, Microsoft Excel, Microsoft PowerPoint, JPEG, PIC files, PDF, MP3, WMV, or QuickTime.

    .question Q. Is there a file size limit for the media gallery?
    p There is no limit to the size of a single file as long as it does not exceed your permanent storage limit.

    .question Q. Can I set up an account for someone else?
    p Many people wish to purchase an account for a child, parent or grandparent and manage it. You can purchase an account to curate another person's life. However, you must have permission, legal authority, or personal or familial ties (in accordance with FOREVER's terms of service) if you are establishing the account in a name other than your own. You would be the active Account Manager for that Permanent Member.

    .question Q. What happens to my guest account if I die before I buy permanent storage?
    p Your account will be deactivated.

